      <p><b>Definition of Array:</b> An array is a linear data structure that stores 
      elements of the same type in continuous memory locations. Each item is accessed using 
      an index, starting from 0 in most languages like C, Java, and Python. 
      Arrays are used to store and access multiple values efficiently, and can be 
      single-dimensional (like a list) or multi-dimensional (like a matrix). 
      They are popular because of their simplicity, speed, and direct memory use.</p>

      <pre><code>int arr[5] = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};</code></pre>

      <p><strong><i class="fas fa-question-circle me-2"></i>Why use Arrays?</strong></p>
